  "texts": [
    "This teleological context differs morally from human embryos.",
    "Purposefully enhancing organoid complexity requires weighing scientific benefits against ethical risks (Farahany et al., 2018).",
    "For instance, xenotransplantation into rodents raises concerns about human neural chimeras (Yang et al., 2020).",
    "While the extent of functionality and sentience remains unsettled, ethical caution may be warranted as engineering aims closer toward recapitulating advanced human neural capabilities.",
    "Cerebral organoids can elicit moral concern based on their human neural cell identity and resemblance to developing brains, unlike other stem cell-derived organoids (Farahany et al., 2018)."
